sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Claude
    participant U as User
    participant S as MCP Server

    Note over C,U: Unknown senders from process_known_senders

    C->>U: Present unknown senders table<br/>(from_address, from_name, subject)
    U->>C: Confirm/adjust classifications

    Note over C,S: Domain Consolidation Check

    loop For each unknown sender domain
        C->>S: list_rules(search: "domain.com")
        S-->>C: Existing rules for this domain

        alt 2+ senders, same domain, same action
            C->>S: evaluate_regex(pattern, action)
            S-->>C: { rule_matches, conflicts, inbox_sample }
            C->>S: add_regex_rule(pattern, action, description)
            S-->>C: { rule_id, pattern, action }
            C->>S: remove_rule(rule_id) × N
            Note over C,S: Remove superseded exact rules
        else Different actions for same domain
            Note over C: Add as exact rule<br/>Note fragmentation for user
        else Regex already covers domain
            Note over C: Confirm with user<br/>before adding redundant rule
        end
    end

    Note over C,S: Bulk Classification

    C->>S: classify_senders([...classifications])
    S-->>C: { saved: N, failed: [], total_rules }

    Note over C,S: Reprocess Newly Classified

    C->>S: process_known_senders(date range)
    S-->>C: { known_processed, unknown_senders[] }
    Note over C: Repeat until no unknowns remain
